node.text:
IT'S THE NPS-AVERSARY!
From the early days of "hey, maybe we should keep this place wild", through pivotal moments of the very fabric of modern American history, the NPS continues to protect and preserve the places that make us who we are. 
Today marks 103 years of National Parks Service – we think a toast is in order! Video by @maxeyfish #radparks #findyourpark

node.title: The (unofficial) History of the National Parks

node.text: We worked with photographer Tommy Corey (@twerkinthedirt) and outdoor enthusiast @KamRedlawsk on a project that exemplifies what we believe in: parks are for all. Kam’s story is unique to her, but represents the kind of voices we think are essential to the outdoor community. Here's a sneak peek! #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

node.text:
Let's talk backpacking! @ncascadesnps is the perfect place to get some mountaineering in, whether you're going on an overnight trip or a week long excursion. When exploring in the backcountry, it's important to follow all rules and regulations of the park, including fire restrictions and camping in designated sites along the trail corridor when available. Been backpacking in North Cascades National Park? Share your story with us in the comments!

Photo by @thenomadicdrifter
📍Photo taken on Nlaka'pamux and Sauk Suiattle native lands. #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter

node.text:
We teamed up with @equatorcoffees to create a special sweatshirt celebrating their newest  Equator location—Roundhouse Cafe!

Anyone who knows us knows we started Parks Project to leave the world better than we found it. Same goes for Equator Coffees—that’s why we've created this limited edition sweatshirt featuring San Francisco favorites 🌉 They are vintage cut, crazy comfortable, and the perfect weight for those days when the fog rolls in thicker than cappuccino foam.

We only made a few, and they’re going fast. Head over to the Equator store now to get yours while you can. #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

node.text:
Leave it better than you found it. It's not just a phrase we say, but words we live by. Our national parks are loved by millions, but they can’t be taken for granted—with your help, we've been able to give back $1,721,020 to parks we all know and love.

That money has funded next generation initiative projects, advocacy and education, wildlife restoration, and trail projects, but that's not all! Check out our contribution link in our bio to explore 42 of our current park projects. #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

node.text:
We love to see siblings getting along! Three Brothers, one of the many iconic rock formations in @Yosemitenps, offers spectacular views of the valley below. The hike to the top is roughly 7 miles, averaging 4.5 hours up and 3.5 hours down, so be sure to plan for a full day of hiking, and don't forget to pack a lunch 🥪  #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark
